news.title: Chandigarh property consultants requests DM to hold hike in collector rates for four months
news.para: Members said since authorities were in the process of increasing collector rates, a grace period would help buyers and sellers who have already entered into agreements to sell, allowing them to close their deals without hassle.

news.title: Bhopal administration extends deadline for objections on property rate hike to March 22
news.para: According to Meek, all the leaders they met have assured them of help and expressed solidarity with their cause as incessant increase in the collector guideline rates of property is hampering the development of the state capital.

news.title: Norway sovereign wealth fund makes $1 billion real estate investments
news.para: Shaftesbury Capital will retain the remaining 75% interest and manage the London portfolio on behalf of the joint venture, while subsidiaries of AXA will hold 60% ownership in the other portfolio.

news.title: Revenue minister chairs meeting on demolition of 65 illegal buildings in Dombivli, Mumbai
news.para: Earlier, the chief minister also said that the state might think of relaxing rules to save genuine home buyers and, if required, the state would move to the Supreme Court.

news.title: Prologis to invest $1 billion in India, doubling its logistics real estate footprint
news.para: India’s logistics and warehousing sector has witnessed unprecedented growth in recent years, aided by major regulatory reforms such as the implementation of the goods and services tax (GST), improvements in compliance rules and significant infrastructure investments.

news.title: Adani Group in advance talks to acquire Emaar India
news.para: Emaar India has a large portfolio of residential and commercial spaces across Delhi-NCR, Mumbai, Mohali, Lucknow, Indore and Jaipur.

news.title: Cement price hikes rolled back amid rising fuel costs
news.para: For cement producers, power and fuel typically account for 22-24 per cent of the production cost, of which petcoke is typically around 15 per cent.

news.title: Homeowners in Karnataka disappointed as new bill on apartment ownership is delayed
news.para: During the last budget session, Shivakumar and the govt had assured legislators that a new, comprehensive law would be introduced to address these concerns. However, no progress has been made so far.

news.title: GDA increases FAR cap to 80% for small industrial plots for SMEs in Ghaziabad
news.para: GDA secretary Rajesh Kumar Singh said the Authority adopted reforms under Centre's ‘Special Assistance to State for Capital Investment' scheme to address the challenges of land scarcity amid rapid industrialisation and urbanisation.

news.title: Builder’s property in Bhopal to be auctioned for Rs 20 lakh RERA dues
news.para: The court asked for the personal presence of the district collector in the previous hearing of the case on March 12, but he moved an application in the court seeking an exemption from appearance on the pretext of some important official work in Delhi.

news.title: Rajkot civic body issues notices regarding fire NOC to 144 buildings
news.para: A similar drive was initiated after the TRP Game Zone fire of May last year, which snuffed out 27 lives. However, the campaign lost steam after a few months.

news.title: Asking tenant to vacate is not defamation: Karnataka HC
news.para: Court states defamation demands intent to harm reputation and highlights unpublished allegedly defamatory statements cannot cause harm without communication to third party

news.title: Noida Authority to crackdown on plot allottees who fail to begin construction or clear dues
news.para: During a departmental review meeting, Noida CEO Lokesh M reviewed the status of previously allotted residential plots where owners have not undertaken any construction or have outstanding payments pending for an extended period.

news.title: Mere ‘legal’ owner of property need not pay capital gains tax: ITAT
news.para: The ITAT emphasized that merely having a name on a property title does not necessarily confer ownership if there is clear evidence to the contrary. Thus, on sale of the property, where the proceeds flow solely to the beneficial owner, the individual whose name has been merely added is not obliged to pay tax on capital gains.

news.title: DDA begins process to demolish Signature View Apartments in Delhi's Mukherjee Nagar
news.para: Delhi Development Authority is hiring an agency to demolish 336 flats at Signature View Apartments over safety concerns. Residents are vacating, but clarity is needed on rent release dates. High Court instructed DDA to vacate and pay rent quickly. DDA's circular outlines vacation procedures, including disconnecting utilities and handling dues.

news.title: Plot owners in Noida have time till March 31 to restore rainwater harvesting units
news.para: Residents were also told to ensure compliance with electric vehicle (EV) charging provisions. From April 1, co-managers of all work circles will begin site inspections to verify compliance.

news.title: Uttarakhand HC junks bail plea of Dehradun builder in Rs 30 crore apartment fraud case
news.para: ​A case was filed against Rajpal Walia by the Enforcement Directorate (ED) under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) and sections 420 and 406 of Indian Penal Code (IPC) in 2021 for financial irregularities linked to a multi-storey apartment project on Sahastradhara Road near Rajpur Road.

news.title: Builder to hand over upkeep to AOA once it's registered: NCLAT
news.para: A bench headed by chairperson of NCLAT Justice Ashok Bhushan said a real estate company has no right to resist handing over of maintenance to the association.

news.title: Greater Noida homebuyers get hope as SC seeks financial details on delayed project
news.para: The apex court criticized the authority for failing to cooperate in the entire exercise of reviving a dead project where the home buyers had been cheated by the builder who had vanished decades ago.

news.title: Odisha HC extends stay on government notification to clear ambiguities in apartment act
news.para: The HC imposed the interim restriction on the operation of the notification on Feb 12 in response to a petition that sought intervention as it allowed non-application of the legislation in the case of apartments completed before the commencement of the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act in the state — prior to Feb 25, 2017.
